        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Eight hours prior to the terrorist attacks, San Francisco Mayor Willie Brown receives a warning from his “security people at the airport,” advising him to be cautious in traveling.  Later reports will claim that this is because someone saw the State Department warning of September 7 , which focused on the threat to military personnel in Asia. Brown is scheduled to fly to New York the next morning.  The source of the warning, and why it is personally issued to Brown, will remain unknown. </p>",
