        "title": "9/11 Hijacker Jarrah Makes Final Phone Call to Girlfriend in Germany",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "6:45 a.m. September 11, 2001: 9/11 Hijacker Jarrah Makes Final Phone Call to Girlfriend in Germany - History Commons\r",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a645jarrahphonecall#a645jarrahphonecall",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Hijacker Ziad Jarrah phones his girlfriend, Aysel Senguen, about an hour before he boards Flight 93, according to the Los Angeles Times. Senguen is currently recovering from a minor operation in a hospital in Germany, where she lives.  Senguen will later recount: “[H]e was very brief. He said he loved me three times. I asked what was up. He hung up shortly afterwards.… It was so short and rather strange him saying that repeatedly.”  Some accounts will say Jarrah makes this call from his hotel, the Days Inn in Newark. Other accounts will claim he makes it from a payphone at Newark Airport, although he does not actually check in at the airport until later on, at 7:39 a.m.  </p>",
