        "title": "Flight 93 Is Delayed for 41 Minutes; Cause Uncertain",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "8:01 a.m. September 11, 2001: Flight 93 Is Delayed for 41 Minutes; Cause Uncertain - History Commons",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a801delay#a801delay",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Flight 93 is delayed for 41 minutes on the runway at Newark Airport, New Jersey. It will take off at 8:42 a.m.  Apparently, it has to wait in a line of about a dozen planes before it can take off.  According to the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette, the delay is partly due to a fire at the airport the previous afternoon that had led to the runways being closed for 34 minutes.  But the 9/11 Commission says it is “because of the airport’s typically heavy morning traffic.”  And the Boston Globe later reports that United Airlines “will not explain why” Flight 93 was delayed on the runway.  NBC News comments, “That delay would give passengers on Flight 93 the time to realize that this was a suicide mission and the chance to thwart it.”  CNN adds that it therefore “likely saved the White House or the US Capitol from destruction.”  </p>",
