        "calc_duration": 0,
        "sort": 0,
        "title": "Boston Flight Control Tells Other Centers about Hijack, but Not NORAD",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "8:25 a.m. September 11, 2001: Boston Flight Control Tells Other Centers about Hijack, but Not NORAD - History Commons",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a825othercenters#a825othercenters",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Boston flight control reportedly “notifies several air traffic control centers that a hijack is taking place.”  This is immediately after Boston controllers heard a transmission from Flight 11, declaring, “We have some planes” . </p>",
        "image": "",
        "image_caption": "",
        "timezone": "EDT",
        "approved": true,
        "media_type": "html",
        "duration": 120,
        "start": 30300,
