        "title": "Flight 11 Attendant Betty Ong Provides Seat Numbers of Two Hijackers",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "8:28 a.m. September 11, 2001: Flight 11 Attendant Betty Ong Provides Seat Numbers of Two Hijackers - History Commons",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a827marquis#a827marquis",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Betty Ong, a flight attendant on Flight 11, tells American Airlines employees on the ground the seat numbers of two hijackers who have gained unauthorized access to the cockpit of her plane.  Ong is on the phone with three members of staff at the American Airlines Southeastern Reservations Office in North Carolina, and has been describing to them the trouble on her plane.  She previously said she thought that two hijackers had forced their way into the cockpit, but could provide no description of them .  </p>",
