        "calc_duration": 0,
        "sort": 0,
        "title": "NORAD Reportedly Notified that Flight 175 Has Been Hijacked, 9/11 Commission Will Dispute This",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "8:43 a.m. September 11, 2001: NORAD Reportedly Notified that Flight 175 Has Been Hijacked, 9/11 Commission Will Dispute This - History Commons",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a843noradnotified#a843noradnotified",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>After 9/11, NORAD and other sources will claim that NORAD’s Northeast Air Defense Sector (NEADS) is notified at this time that Flight 175 has been hijacked.  However, the FAA’s New York Center, which is handling Flight 175, first alerts its military liaison about the hijacking at around 9:01 .  </p>",
