        "calc_duration": 0,
        "sort": 0,
        "title": "NORAD Public Affairs Officer Calls Brother in WTC; Possibly Warns Him of Second Hijacked Plane",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "8:53 a.m. September 11, 2001: NORAD Public Affairs Officer Calls Brother in WTC; Possibly Warns Him of Second Hijacked Plane - History Commons\r",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a853ariascallswtc#a853ariascallswtc",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Major Don Arias, the public affairs officer for NORAD, has just learned of the first WTC crash from television and a phone call from NEADS . Adam Arias reacts to his brother’s call with urgency, going around the floor exhorting people to leave, and physically throwing one woman out of her office. Several survivors will later credit him with saving their lives.  Adam Arias will be killed when the South Tower collapses.  </p>",
        "image": "http://cdn.historycommons.org/images/events/800_adam_arias_2050081722-13306-1.jpg",
        "image_caption": "Adam Arias ",
        "timezone": "EDT",
