        "sort": 0,
        "title": "NEADS Requests Refueling Planes from McGuire Air Force Base",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "9:04 a.m. September 11, 2001: NEADS Requests Refueling Planes from McGuire Air Force Base - History Commons",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a904mcguiretankers#a904mcguiretankers",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>NORAD’s Northeast Air Defense Sector (NEADS) contacts McGuire Air Force Base in New Jersey and asks if it has any tanker planes available that would be able to support the fighter jets that took off in response to the hijacking of Flight 11 and McGuire says it has two tankers currently airborne that are carrying plenty of fuel.  Two F-15 fighters took off from Otis Air National Guard Base in Cape Cod, Massachusetts, at 8:46 a.m. .  </p>",
