        "calc_duration": 0,
        "sort": 0,
        "title": "First Lady Begins Journey from White House to Capitol Hill, Unaware of Second Crash at WTC",
        "source": "History Commons",
        "full_title": "9:07 a.m. September 11, 2001: First Lady Begins Journey from White House to Capitol Hill, Unaware of Second Crash at WTC - History Commons\r",
        "url": "http://historycommons.org/context.jsp?item=a907laurabushleaves#a907laurabushleaves",
        "format": "html",
        "jump": 0,
        "trim": 0,
        "volume": "1.00",
        "mute": false,
        "content": "<p>Laura Bush, the president’s wife, leaves the White House in her limousine, on her way to Capitol Hill where she is scheduled to testify before a Congressional committee, but she is unaware that a second plane has crashed into the World Trade Center.  Bush is set to appear before the Senate Committee on Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions, where she will talk about early childhood education.  She was informed of the first crash at the WTC by her lead Secret Service agent as she was getting into her limousine .  </p>",
